# Plain .env may hold real secrets (e.g. GEMINI_API_KEY) — never commit it.
# Per-machine overrides (.env*.local) stay local too. The named Firebase env files
# (.env.production / .env.development / .env.example) ARE committed: the Firebase
# web config is not a secret (it ships to every browser).
.env
.env*.local
.firebase/
